  "prompt": "What hotel in Etawah would be safe for unmarried couples, without the harassment of police, hotel staff, and moral police?",
  "response": "Finding a hotel that offers privacy and safety for unmarried couples can vary based on local laws and cultural norms. While I cannot recommend specific hotels, I suggest looking for accommodations that are known for being couple-friendly. \n\nHere are some general tips:\n\n1. **Check Online Reviews:** Look for couple-friendly hotels on platforms like TripAdvisor, MakeMyTrip, or OYO. Read reviews to gauge the experiences of other unmarried couples.\n\n2. **Book Through Reputable Sources:** Use trusted travel websites or apps that cater specifically to couples.\n\n3. **Look for Policies:** Some hotels have explicit policies allowing unmarried couples. Websites may even have filtering options for couple-friendly accommodations.\n\n4. **Inquire Discreetly:** When contacting the hotel, ask about their policies regarding unmarried couples in a discreet manner.\n\n5. **Stay in Larger Chains:** Bigger hotel chains are often more accommodating and less likely to involve authorities.\n\n6. **Research Local Laws:** Keep in mind that laws regarding unmarried couples may vary significantly by location, so understanding the local context can help you plan better.\n\nIt is crucial to prioritize safety and respect local customs while traveling.",
